    <bioghist>United States Senator from Michigan, 1857-1875 and 1879, and Secretary of the Interior, 1875-1877.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>Correspondence (principally letters received before 1879) relating to the politics of the Civil War and Reconstruction from Chandler's vantage point as a member of the Joint Comittee on the Conduct of the War and as chairman of the Committee on Commerce; also materials on early political activity in Michigan. Correspondents include: J. A. J. Creswell, G. A. Custer, Marsh Giddings, U. S. Grant, and B. F. Wade.</scopecontent>
